[hr][/hr]

[h2]💡 Design Philosophy[/h2]
Waymakers don't care about conquest or isolation. They get their joy from movement, commerce, and cooperation, and they get uneasy when the colony goes quiet and the roads go untouched. To them, a civilization isn't defined by its walls, but by the roads that connect it to everyone else.

[h2]🐛 Known Limitations[/h2]
[list]
[*]"Isolated Settlement" mood thought is planned but not yet implemented.
[*]Road destruction has no clean hook in RotR yet, so the "Route Destroyed" thought is back burnered.
[/list]

[h2]❤️ Support[/h2]
Found a bug or have a suggestion? Drop it in the comments or the Discussions tab. This mod is actively maintained.

